Hypot hesi s
Is som e content suited to tik tok style (specific to our research) m ore than
others?
Tik Tok Style is better suited than other styles to communicate factual
information. Comparatively, articles are better at communicating
conceptual information.
How much (quantitatively) of an effect can the use of tik tok style improve the
awareness, general understanding of orcas?
Tik Tok Style will sufficiently improve the awareness of the topic but
would only slightly improve the understanding of orcas.

Types of Quest i ons
1. Awareness (Memory -sort of)
Only requires participant to know of topic
Example: Female octopuses are often smaller than the male octopuses.
1. Understanding
Require participant to apply contextual knowledge to question
Example: Anglerfishes often wiggle their esca (a dangling body part) to help
with fluid movement.

Hypot hesi s Test i ng
Hypothesis:
H_0 : F_A(x) = F_B(x) = F_C(x)
where A: articles, B:Informal Videos, C: Formal Videos
H_A: F_i(x) <= F_j(x) or F_i(x) >= F_j(x)
for some i is not equal to j {A,B,C}
Kruskall-Wal l i s Test
-Non-parametric approach
-Uses ranks
p_val = 0.868 > alpha at any reasonable level (ie. 0.01, 0.05, 0.1)
Fail to reject H_0
There's insufficient evidence to conclude H_a (there's differences between
the 3 groups in terms of the scores).
Mul t ipl e Comparisons
all. diff denotes for the differences between the average ranks
all.BON denotes for the Bonferroni cutoffs
all.HSD denotes for the Turkeys Honest Significant Difference cutoffs
Cutoffs are all larger than the differences between the mean value of the ranks
--> no significant difference between the groups
Reflection
What we have accomplished:
We had 37 participants who completed the Pre-Su r v e y
We had 18 participants who watched the video/read the article and
completed the post survey; Around 90% of them finished all of 3
materials
Reflection
What we could have fixed:
Lack of participants
More controlled settings (randomized in terms of knowledge instead
of major)
More Questions (to better test participants knowledge)
Better Questions (more in-depth)
